cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.CC, cs.PL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal language theory and automata theory, which are closely related to logic. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper explicitly mentions automata theory and establishes pumping lemmas for quantum B\"uchi automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper studies the closure properties of languages accepted by QBAs in different semantics, which is related to complexity theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are less likely categories, but still possible as the paper deals with formal language theory and automata theory, which are foundational topics in computer science and relevant to programming languages and data structures/algorithms.
